,"1324":"1324","1246":"1246","1355":"1355","1289":"1289","about 1325":"omkring 1325","0132":"0132","1320":"1320","1317":"1317","Leslie Castle, Auchleven, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Auchleven, Aberdeenshire, Skotland, United Kingdom","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Skotland, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"about 1291–about 1325":"circa 1291–circa 1325","1280–1324":"1280–1324","1283–Female":"1283–Overleden","1290–1350":"1290–1350","1291–1325":"1291–1325","–Male":"Overleden","1289–1355":"1289–1355","0132–1382":"0132–1382","1246–1317":"1246–1317","1250–1320":"1250–1320","about 1291":"circa 1291","1350":"1350","1250":"1250","1382":"1382","1283":"1283","Bef 1317":"vóór 1317","1291":"1291","1280":"1280","1290":"1290","1325":"1325","1324":"1324","1246":"1246","1355":"1355","1289":"1289","about 1325":"circa 1325","0132":"0132","1320":"1320","1317":"1317","Leslie Castle, Auchleven, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Auchleven, Aberdeenshire, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"about 1291–about 1325":"about 1291–about 1325","1280–1324":"1280–1324","1283–Female":"1283–Deceased","1290–1350":"1290–1350","1291–1325":"1291–1325","–Male":"Deceased","1289–1355":"1289–1355","0132–1382":"0132–1382","1246–1317":"1246–1317","1250–1320":"1250–1320","about 1291":"about 1291","1350":"1350","1250":"1250","1382":"1382","1283":"1283","Bef 1317":"before 1317","1291":"1291","1280":"1280","1290":"1290","1325":"1325","1324":"1324","1246":"1246","1355":"1355","1289":"1289","about 1325":"about 1325","0132":"0132","1320":"1320","1317":"1317","Leslie Castle, Auchleven, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Auchleven, Aberdeenshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Leslie","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from a barony in Aberdeenshire, which is first recorded <i>c.</i> 1180 in the form <i>Lesslyn</i>, of obscure origin. Leslie in Fife is said to be named for this place; in some cases the surname may come from there.","English: from the Middle English female personal name <i>Lecelin</i>, a double diminutive of <i>Lece</i>. See   Leece   and   Lesley  .","History: The Scottish Clan Leslie claims descent from Bartolf, a Hungarian nobleman who came to Scotland in 1068 or 1070 in the retinue of Queen Margaret. She was an English princess who had been born and brought up in Hungary and who went on to marry King Malcolm III of Scotland. Members of the clan have held several titles in the peerage of Scotland, including Earl of Rothes (from 1437)."],"variants":[{"name":"Leece","meanings":["English: from a medieval female personal name, <i>Lece</i>, a short form of <i>Lettice</i> (from Latin <i>Laetitia</i>, meaning ‘happiness, gaiety’).","English: variant of   Lees  .","Irish: shortened form of Gaelic <i>Mac Giolla Íosa</i>, Manx <i>Mac Guilley Yeesey</i> ‘son of <i>Giolla Íosa</i> (devotee or servant of Jesus)’. Ballaleece (‘Leece's farm’) in Kirk German was the family's main seat."]},{"name":"Lesslie","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Leslie  ."]},{"name":"Lesley","meanings":["Scottish and northern Irish: variant of   Leslie  ."]},{"name":"Laslie","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Leslie  ."]},{"name":"Lessley","meanings":["English (Norfolk): variant of   Leslie  ."]},{"name":"Lasley","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Leslie  ."]}]},{"name":"Andrew","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of the Greek name <i>Andreas</i>, a short form of any of various compound names derived from <i>andr-</i> ‘man, warrior’. In the New Testament this is the name of the first disciple to be called by Jesus. After the Resurrection,  St Andrew  preached in Asia Minor and Greece. He is traditionally believed to have been crucified at Patras in Achaia. He was one of the most popular saints of the Middle Ages and was adopted as the patron of Scotland, Russia, and Greece. It has long been among the most popular boys' names in the English-speaking world, especially in Scotland. Its popularity in England was further enhanced by its use as a British royal name for  Prince Andrew  (  b. 1960 ), the Duke of York."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Andrew Leslie 6th Dominus Ejusdem was born about 1291, in Scotland, United Kingdom, his father, Sir Norman Leslie Of That Ilk, was 47 and his mother, Elizabeth Leith, was 42. He had at least 1 son with Mary de Abernethy. He died about 1325, in his hometown, at the age of 36."},"et":{"about 1291–about 1325":"umbes 1291–umbes 1325","1280–1324":"1280–1324","1283–Female":"1283–Surnud","1290–1350":"1290–1350","1291–1325":"1291–1325","–Male":"Surnud","1289–1355":"1289–1355","0132–1382":"0132–1382","1246–1317":"1246–1317","1250–1320":"1250–1320","about 1291":"umbes 1291","1350":"1350","1250":"1250","1382":"1382","1283":"1283","Bef 1317":"enne 1317","1291":"1291","1280":"1280","1290":"1290","1325":"1325","1324":"1324","1246":"1246","1355":"1355","1289":"1289","about 1325":"umbes 1325","0132":"0132","1320":"1320","1317":"1317","Leslie Castle, Auchleven, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Auchleven, Aberdeenshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1291–about 1325":"noin 1291–noin 1325","1280–1324":"1280–1324","1283–Female":"1283–Kuollut","1290–1350":"1290–1350","1291–1325":"1291–1325","–Male":"Kuollut","1289–1355":"1289–1355","0132–1382":"0132–1382","1246–1317":"1246–1317","1250–1320":"1250–1320","about 1291":"noin 1291","1350":"1350","1250":"1250","1382":"1382","1283":"1283","Bef 1317":"ennen vuotta 1317","1291":"1291","1280":"1280","1290":"1290","1325":"1325","1324":"1324","1246":"1246","1355":"1355","1289":"1289","about 1325":"noin 1325","0132":"0132","1320":"1320","1317":"1317","Leslie Castle, Auchleven, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Auchleven, Aberdeenshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistyn